Discussion/Conclusion

We see that as age increases, playerâs only become more successful in the Premier League. However, based on the data and results shown, it appears that the Premier League doesnât show that the relationship between age and success metric is parabolic or squared. This is maybe because the premier league is top tier. Players that age older get removed from the premier league, so we donât get to see them drop off. This is why we see great players like Messi, go to lower leagues such as the MLS (shame to say). Therefore, itâs safe to assume that when players reach around the 35 year old mark, they transfer out of the Premier League and into different, âlower-levelâ leagues.
